{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Playwright Test Type Suggestion",
  "description": "Suggests Playwright E2E tests when creating new test files, especially for integration or browser-related tests",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileCreated",
    "patterns": [
      "tests/**/*.test.ts",
      "tests/**/*.spec.ts"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "New test file created! Consider the appropriate testing approach:\n\n🧪 **Test Type Decision Tree:**\n\n**Unit Tests (Vitest)** ✅ Use when:\n- Testing isolated functions/classes\n- Pure logic without browser APIs\n- Fast feedback needed\n- Mocking is acceptable\n\n**E2E Tests (Playwright)** 🎭 Use when:\n- Testing browser features (Workers, Storage, etc.)\n- Verifying UI interactions\n- Checking console output\n- Testing real browser behavior\n- Integration of multiple systems\n- Performance/memory testing\n\n📁 **File location guide:**\n- `tests/unit/` → Vitest unit tests\n- `tests/integration/` → Vitest integration tests (mocked browser)\n- `tests/e2e/` → Playwright E2E tests (real browser)\n- `tests/bugfix/` → Regression tests (choose based on bug type)\n\n🎯 **Recent success story:**\nWe found a critical bug (90x WorkerPool creation) using Playwright that would have been impossible to catch with unit tests alone!\n\n💡 **Playwright test location:**\nCreate E2E tests in `tests/e2e/` with `.spec.ts` extension\n\n**Does this test need real browser behavior?** If yes → Use Playwright!"
  }
}